This guys is frightened of everything possible. His phobias include: Rats, bats, heights, water, spiders, ghosts, zombies, the dark, pixies for some reason, snakes, anything involving 13, and thunderstorms. If any of these come within seeing or hearing range of the rogue, he hightails it back to the nearest exit, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">screaming</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> at the top of his lungs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Clumsy/Unlucky Monk</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This monk is the posterchild for insurance companies. The worst thing that could possibly happen to him usually does. He trips, falls, and breaks things (often of great value) of such great frequency that he's virtually bankrupted constantly. He will often go in and out of Feign Death for no reason what so ever. His weapons will fumble out of his hands in combat, and he gets lost, even with a compass surgically grafted to his spinal cord, ALL THE TIME. If a human, he'd have to be pathetically nice and apologetic, but if an Iksar, he'd have to be constantly embarassed, cursing, and claiming that every mishap is done on purpose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Homebody Druidess</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Without a doubt, this MUST be a Halfling Woman. She is the ultimate grandma. She's without equal in tradeskills, but is adorably timid and mousy, always sighing and saying &quot;Oh Dear!&quot; or &quot;Oh my heavens!&quot; or &quot;Bless my stars!&quot; whenever she accidentally nukes some poor creature. She constantly worries over people's eating habits and health, and persistantly sneaks/shoves cookies and food into people's faces if she thinks they havn't eaten enough. And no one ever has. Ever. She's also very helpful, and will give her last copper away if it means some poor stranger can buy that new shield he always wanted. She's the lady who makes us all warm and fuzzy, and say, &quot;Aw.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Crotchety Gnome Caster</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Should be a Gnome, but any magic class will do. The Grinch Gnomified, ornery to the core and downright nasty at times. He acts mean spirited, but is in truth an old, lonely man who just wants someone to talk to, despite his protests otherwise. Always talks about &quot;the day,&quot; when everything was a thousand times mare difficult, boring, and time-consuming. A frequent napper, because his bad hip is constantly acting up. The Gnomish Old Boot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Virgilian Warrior</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
He may have the body of a warrior, but he has the heart and soul of a poet. Everything he says is in Epic Verse, Dactyllic Hexameter, Haiku, Sonnets, Limmericks, Rhyms, and etc. Epic Metaphores are created ad lib constantly, especially in the heat of battle. A poet above all, will often spend hours on end perfecting his latest craft, meditating on a cliffside. His sole purpose as a Warrior is to see the world in its entirety so that he might write the most Epic Poem of all, which will be his Magnum Opus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=larraquemeleagrance>Larraque Meleagrance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.teamxbox.com/avatar.php?userid=6484&dateline=1044513211" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Radical Dreamer</span><br>  Posts: 1063<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 9:27:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4182.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forums.teamxbox.com/avatar.php?userid=6484&dateline=1044513211 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: And some more...</span><hr size=1> I just want to do a raid of bards. Only bards. And nothing but Bards.<br>
